# Context Core, Not Another RAG

This repository is a minimal context operating core, not a generic RAG
framework, chat app, agent demo, or wrapper around vendor SDKs.

## Rule

Every design and implementation decision must preserve this direction:

```text
deterministic project memory
  -> precise indexing
  -> hybrid retrieval
  -> source-backed ContextPack
  -> typed tool/model/subagent step
  -> verification
  -> replayable trace
```

## Guardrails

- No extra code without a roadmap/progress chunk, invariant, adapter boundary, or
  failing test that justifies it.
- No extra request: avoid broad crawling, unbounded model calls, repeated
  retrieval, or background work without a task, budget, owner, and trace.
- No extra dependency: prefer standard library and internal interfaces until a
  measured need requires an adapter.
- Do not start with "vector search + prompt". Start with source identity,
  artifact storage, chunk spans, checksums, manifests, sparse/exact retrieval,
  and provenance.
- Do not trust LLM output as source truth. Model output may summarize, plan, or
  draft only after evidence is selected and traceable.
- Do not let agent orchestration drive the domain model. Agents sit on top of
  project memory, retrieval, context packs, tools, policy, and verification.
- Keep classic deterministic IR first-class: exact search, sparse/BM25-style
  search, phrase/proximity path, morphology hooks, fuzzy matching, and
  source-span lookup.
- Keep provider choices replaceable: QDrant, PostgreSQL, object storage, LLMs,
  rerankers, crawlers, and product integrations are adapters.

## Review Question

Before accepting a change, ask:

> Does this make the core more precise, auditable, minimal, and replayable, or
> does it move the project toward another opaque RAG framework?
